    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process by which clay is prepared for throwing; consists of cutting sections of clay with a wire and then pounding or kneading by hand to expel air pockets and to make the consistency of the clay more pliable.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
